    paper_abstract: 'Over the last decade, in seminars, conferences, and workshops, Peter Tittenberger and I have had the opportunity to explore the role of technology in transforming learning. From conversations during these engagements, a set of concerns has emerged: 1. Educators express interest in improving their teaching and learning practices, particularly emphasizing the need to improve engagement of learners (online or in-class). 2. While concerned about improving teaching and learning, educators generally resist: a. Advanced pedagogical discussions that are not readily transferable to the online or face-to-face classroom b. Technology-heavy hype and suggestions that the social element of learning can somehow be replaced.',
